properties.areaDesc: Indian Wells Valley; Kern County Desert
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 14 at 4:31AM PST until January 14 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 50 mph.

* WHERE...Indian Wells Valley and Kern County Desert.

* WHEN...Until 10 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds can make travel difficult, particularly
for high profile vehicles. Winds could blow around unsecured
objects. Tree limbs could be blown down, resulting in a few
power outages.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Occasional gusts near 50 mph mainly
around Mojave during the night. Gusty winds will increase
below the mountain passes Tuesday with gusts up to 55 mph
during the afternoon. Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 14, Highway 178 below Walker Pass, and
Highway 58 below Tehachapi Pass, including the town of Mojave.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING
